      "description": "Solid project car with good bones and a surprisingly willing drivetrain. Engine starts, runs, and pulls with respectable torque, and the transmission engages as it should. Steering, braking, and suspension feel usable for a budget build, parts runner, or weekend revival. Cosmetically it shows age and needs attention, but underneath it presents as an honest, complete driver with plenty of upside for someone who knows their way around basic maintenance. Great candidate for a dependable beater, flip, or mechanical refresh.",
